&lt;h1&gt;Lead Cancer Nurse - B8b&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Royal United Hospital is looking to appoint an exceptional talent to the key senior role of Lead Cancer Nurse for the Trust!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a proactive, innovative clinical leader with a passion for delivering a high quality of care then we would welcome your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With substantial experience in a senior clinical role and a wealth of knowledge of cancer services, this role will see you providing clinical leadership to the cancer nursing workforce ensuring the delivery of the Trust cancer strategy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With a proven track record in collaborative working and an ability to engage and motivate teams to deliver high quality care and services with the patient at the centre. You will demonstrate clear influential leadership to shape and deliver cancer services across the Trust and in within the RUH catchment area in line with the Trust values and respect behaviours and the national strategies. You will provide expert advice and guidance to internal and external stakeholders on the direction of cancer care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We would encourage applications from those staff who would thrive given the opportunity to be part of a team furthering the excellent reputation of the Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mr Jon McFarlane, Assoicate Medical Director for Cancer on 01225821791&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amanda Gell, Divisional Director for Nursing for Women and Children’s Division on 01225825543&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ed Nicolle, Interim Deputy Divisional Director for Operations for Women and Children&#39;s Division on 01225 824042. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
